** About our Professional Services Consulting opportunity: **

  * Want to grow your career driving business outcomes with your business consulting experience in delivering successful ERP solutions? 
  * Do you enjoy utilising your interpersonal, communication and stakeholder management skills? 
  * How about in a well-established and mature Australian software development and vendor company with more than 1500 clients and nearly 500 staff? 
  * Support and collaboration with your team-mates? We’re a friendly bunch. 
  * Hybrid Work Arrangement: find some flexibility in your working week in consultation with your team (the best of both worlds!) 

  
** Where you’d be working: **

This Consultant role will be based in our newly renovated Brisbane office. The
consulting team includes professional services, project managers, business
solutions, support and sales. The team work closely with customers including
onsite visits to undertake customer requirements.

  
** What you’d be doing (your day will look like this): **

Your business consulting skills and experience in a Finance environment will
assist you in this role. Using your knowledge of business processes, following
our implementation methodology and working closely with our Project Managers,
our Professional Services Consultants are responsible for:

  * Implementing Pronto Xi 
  * Facilitating workshops to gather business requirements 
  * Designing solutions to meet with those requirements 
  * Document system configurations 
  * Perform system testing 
  * Deliver end user training 
  * Manage customer business improvements 

** We’re looking for a new Professional Services Consultant who has: **

  * Strong Business Consulting skills and able to demonstrate a strong commercial understanding 
  * Strong ability to design solutions to meet with client’s business requirements 
  * Full lifecycle implementation and upgrade experience in mid to large scale ERP projects 
  * Pronto Xi experience and skills will be highly regarded 
  * Well developed prioritisation and time management skills 
  * Excellent communication skills, written and client facing 
  * Excellent stakeholder, issue, scope management skills 
  * Ability to identify risks and potential issues at an early stage and to be highly competent in bringing these to resolution 
  * Be energetic and enthusiastic, with a desire to make an impact within a consulting environment 

** To enjoy being a Pronto Software Employee you’d need to have: **

  * Successfully completed a degree in Business related discipline or relevant industry experience 
  * Professional membership preferred 
  * You will possess a strong work ethic 
  * You will be resourceful and innovative at tackling complex and business challenges 
  * Work well in a team environment 
  * Ability to influence internal and external stake holders 
  * Excellent attention to detail 
  * Passionate about customer service and delivery excellence 
  * A current driver’s license as travel to customer sites is required 
  * A passport as potential interstate and international travel may be required 

** What you will get: **

  * Earn a salary commensurate with your experience plus a range of employee benefits 
  * Work in a modern, dynamic and friendly team environment 
  * A hybrid working environment (split your week, flexible location arrangements) 
  * The ability to develop your career and experience 

Note: Our employees need to undergo a Police Check

